# Euclid Example: Real-World Applications

This example demonstrates how to use Euclid for real-world mathematical expressions.

## Physics

### Kinetic Energy
KE = (1 / 2) * m * pow(v, 2)

### Einstein's Mass-Energy Equivalence
E = m * pow(c, 2)

### Ohm's Law
V = I * R

### Gravitational Force
F = G * (m1 * m2) / pow(r, 2)

## Statistics

### Sample Mean
mean = sum(x_i, i, 1, n) / n

### Sample Variance
variance = sum(pow((x_i - mean), 2), i, 1, n) / (n - 1)

### Standard Deviation
std_dev = sqrt(variance)

### Normal Distribution Probability Density
f(x) = (1 / (sigma * sqrt(2 * PI))) * exp(-pow((x - mu), 2) / (2 * pow(sigma, 2)))

## Geometry

### Pythagorean Theorem
pow(a, 2) + pow(b, 2) = pow(c, 2)

### Area of Circle
A = PI * pow(r, 2)

### Volume of Sphere
V = (4 / 3) * PI * pow(r, 3)

### Distance Formula in 2D
d = sqrt(pow((x2 - x1), 2) + pow((y2 - y1), 2))

## Finance

### Compound Interest
A = P * pow((1 + r / n), (n * t))

### Present Value
PV = FV / pow((1 + r), t)

## Trigonometry

### Law of Cosines
pow(c, 2) = pow(a, 2) + pow(b, 2) - 2 * a * b * cos(GAMMA)

### Sine Rule
a / sin(ALPHA) = b / sin(BETA) = c / sin(GAMMA)

## Probability and Statistics

Probability: prob(A)
Expected value: expect(X)
Variance: var(X)
Covariance: cov(X, Y)
Bayes' theorem: prob(given(A, B)) = (prob(given(B, A)) * prob(A)) / prob(B)

## Visual Notation

Boxed result: boxed(E = m * c^2)
Cancelled term: cancel(x)
Underbrace: underbrace(a + b + c, "n terms")
Overbrace: overbrace(x_1 + x_2 + ldots + x_n, "n terms")

## Computer Science

### Big O Notation (logarithmic)
T(n) = O(log(n, 2))

### Big O Notation (polynomial)
T(n) = O(pow(n, 2))

### Fibonacci Sequence (closed form)
F(n) = (pow(PHI, n) - pow((1 - PHI), n)) / sqrt(5)
